-- Capital One profit rises 8 pct on card growth
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bangalore
-- Thu Jul 17, 2014 04:18PM EDT
-- None



July 17 (Reuters) - Capital One Financial Corp <COF.N>, one of the largest U.S. credit card issuers, reported an 8 percent rise in quarterly profit as card loans grew and credit quality remained stable.

The company's net income attributable to common stockholders rose to $1.18 billion, or $2.04 per share, in the second quarter ended June 30, from $1.09 billion, or $1.85 per share, a year earlier. [ID:nPn3T59zm]